'''''Mons''''' or '''''Montes''''' are [[Latin]] words used by [[planetary geology|planetary geologists]] (reference the entire list [[Planetary nomenclature#Descriptor Terms .28Feature Types.29|here]]) to refer to [[mountains]] or [[extinct volcano]]es on [[planet]]s and [[natural satellite|moon]]s.  Examples of both uses are [[Maxwell Montes]] ([[Venus]]) and [[Olympus Mons]] ([[Mars]]).

